  "workflow": "1. Identify asset formats in source game\n2. Implement parsers for each format\n3. Convert to web-native formats (glTF, WebP, OGG)\n4. Build archive extraction (ZIP)\5. Create asset loading API\n6. Test with game assets",
  "keyConcepts": [
    "Blitz3D mesh formats (B3D, XFile, RMESH)",
    "Texture formats (BMP, PNG, TGA)",
    "Archive formats (ZIP with zlib)",
    "Coordinate and UV conversion",
    "Animation data extraction"
  ],
  "commonIssues": [
    "Missing or corrupted asset files",
    "Incorrect UV mapping after conversion",
    "Animation bone hierarchies not preserved",
    "File path case sensitivity issues",
    "Large asset file sizes"
  ],
